{"books":{"29":{"id":"1870","title":"Candide ou L'optimisme","description":"<p>Candide vivait paisible et innocent chez le baron de Thunder-ten-tronckh, en Westphalie. Dans son ch\u00e2teau, le pr\u00e9cepteur Pangloss (\u00ab qui discourt de tout \u00bb en grec), repr\u00e9sentation de Gottfried Leibniz, professait un optimisme b\u00e9at. Candide partageait cette pl\u00e9nitude d\u2019autant plus qu\u2019il \u00e9tait amoureux de Cun\u00e9gonde, fille du baron. Un jour, ce m\u00eame baron surprend leurs amours et chasse Candide \u00e0 coups de pied \u00ab dans le derri\u00e8re \u00bb. <br\/>(R\u00e9sum\u00e9 par Wikip\u00e9dia)<\/p> <p>This novella tells the tale of a young man, Candide (meaning \"ingenuous\"), who has been indoctrinated with Leibnizian optimism but becomes disillusioned after witnessing and experiencing many great hardships. <br\/>(Summary from Wikipedia)<\/p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.gutenberg.org\/ebooks\/4650","language":"French","copyright_year":"1759","num_sections":"30","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/1870","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/candide_ou_loptimisme_b_librivox\/candide_ou_loptimisme_b_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"http:\/\/fr.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Candide","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/candide-by-voltaire-2\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"3:52:57","totaltimesecs":13977,"authors":[{"id":"4298","first_name":"","last_name":"Voltaire","dob":"1694","dod":"1778"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/candide_ou_loptimisme_b_librivox","sections":[{"id":"153858","section_number":"1","title":"Chapter 01","listen_url":"http:\/\/upload.librivox.org\/share\/uploads\/ez\/candide_01_voltaire.mp3http:\/\/upload.librivox.org\/share\/uploads\/ez\/candide_01_voltaire.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"382","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"1840","display_name":"Bernard"}]},{"id":"153859","section_number":"2","title":"Chapter 02","listen_url":"http:\/\/upload.librivox.org\/